🛒 Online Retail Data Analysis Project
📌 Project Overview

This project analyzes an online retail dataset to uncover valuable business insights related to customer behavior, sales performance, and product trends. The goal is to transform raw transactional data into meaningful insights using data cleaning, SQL, Python, and visualization tools.

📊 Dataset Description

The dataset contains transactional data of an online retail store. Each record represents a product purchased by a customer.

🔑 Columns Included:

InvoiceNo – Unique transaction ID

StockCode – Product/item code

Description – Product name

Quantity – Number of items purchased

InvoiceDate – Date and time of purchase

UnitPrice – Price per item

CustomerID – Unique customer ID

Country – Customer location

🎯 Objectives

Clean and preprocess raw data

Perform exploratory data analysis (EDA)

Identify top-selling products and countries

Analyze customer purchasing behavior

Perform RFM (Recency, Frequency, Monetary) analysis

Create interactive dashboards

🛠️ Tools & Technologies

Excel – Initial data exploration

MySQL – Data cleaning & querying

Python (Pandas, Matplotlib, Seaborn) – Data analysis

Tableau / Power BI – Data visualization

🧹 Data Cleaning Steps

Removed missing values (CustomerID)

Filtered out negative or zero quantities

Removed duplicate records

Converted date columns into proper format

📈 Key Analysis Performed

Sales trend over time

Top products by revenue

Country-wise sales distribution

Customer segmentation using RFM

Monthly revenue analysis

📊 Dashboard & Visualization

Interactive dashboards created using Tableau / Power BI

KPIs included:

Total Revenue

Total Orders

Top Customers

Best-Selling Products

